    <note>Fan(2) Shouyu [16794] According to the funerary inscription for his great grandson, Yisun [3280] (q.v.), his ancestors were Jinan, Licheng residents and Shouyu moved to the capital. Yisun died in his private residence in Kaifeng although he was buried in Luoyang. Shouyu's son, Zhi [8041], is identified as a Daming, Zongcheng (modern Weixian(b)) resident as are Zhi's son, Min [577], and nephew, Gao [7024]. I am accepting the Daming origins and Shouyu moves from Daming to Kaifeng: the funerary inscription version may reflect 2 moves.</note>
